# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Safe place for tokens (never commit real values)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1) Copy this file to **`.env`** in the same directory as `docker-compose.yml` (repo root, e.g. `~/SYGNIF/.env`).
# 2) That **`.env`** file is listed in **`.gitignore`** — put API keys, bot tokens, and secrets there only.
# 3) Optional extra local files (also gitignored): **`.env.local`**, **`.env.secrets`** — same `KEY=value` lines; load order depends on the tool (Docker Compose uses `env_file: .env` by default).
# 4) Do **not** paste secrets into tracked files (`config.json` in git, README, Telegram, etc.).
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Copy to .env and fill in. Used by docker-compose, notification_handler, and systemd dashboard units.
# Optional: comma-separated compose profiles so `docker compose up -d` starts profiled services after reboot
# (e.g. permanent Nautilus BTC grid: add ``btc-grid-mm`` — see docker-compose ``nautilus-grid-btc01``).
# COMPOSE_PROFILES=btc-nautilus,btc-grid-mm
# Legacy multi-pair spot+futures (archived profile, not in default COMPOSE_PROFILES):
#   docker compose --profile archived-main-traders up -d freqtrade freqtrade-futures
#   Snapshots: archive/freqtrade-main-traders-*/ ; restore FT_SPOT_URL/FT_FUTURES_URL to freqtrade:8080 / freqtrade-futures:8081

# Optional: path to primary secrets file loaded **before** this `.env` (same as docker-compose `x-sygnif-env-files`).
# Later file wins on duplicate keys — put Nautilus poll limits here or in `.env`; keep API keys in the secrets file.
# SYGNIF_SECRETS_ENV_FILE=/home/ubuntu/xrp_claude_bot/.env

# Bybit (Freqtrade)
BYBIT_API_KEY=
BYBIT_API_SECRET=

# Bybit **Demo Trading** API (https://www.bybit.com/demo-trading) — used by Freqtrade demo configs,
# Nautilus live demo adapters, trade-overseer hedge helpers, etc.
BYBIT_DEMO_API_KEY=
BYBIT_DEMO_API_SECRET=
# Optional: **second** Bybit demo API key for Nautilus Grid MM — keeps grid isolated from other demo linear bots
# (same `BYBIT_DEMO_*` otherwise = one shared demo wallet). Create another key in demo UI.
# BYBIT_DEMO_GRID_API_KEY=
# BYBIT_DEMO_GRID_API_SECRET=
# BTC **Interface** (Bybit demo read-only) is served on **BTC Terminal** port — `http://…:8888/interface` (same `sygnif-dashboard-btc-terminal` unit; exclusive with spot on 8888).
# SYGNIF_BTC_IFACE_SYMBOL=BTCUSDT
# SYGNIF_BTC_IFACE_USE_GRID_KEYS=1
# Optional: run `dashboard_server_btc_interface.py` alone for debugging on another port:
# SYGNIF_DASHBOARD_BTC_INTERFACE_PORT=8894
# Nautilus **GridMarketMaker** on Bybit demo (`run_bybit_demo_grid_market_maker.py`, compose `nautilus-grid-btc01`):
# `NAUTILUS_GRID_MM_DEMO_ACK=YES` plus either `BYBIT_DEMO_GRID_*` or `BYBIT_DEMO_*`, e.g.:
# NAUTILUS_GRID_MM_DEMO_ACK=YES
NAUTILUS_GRID_MM_DEMO_ACK=
# freqtrade-btc-spot (profile archived-freqtrade-btc-dock): merge api-demo + demo keys at container start (see user_data/apply_bybit_demo_to_btc_spot_config.py)
# SYGNIF_BTC_SPOT_USE_BYBIT_DEMO=1
# Freqtrade BTC 0.1 futures demo: merge into gitignored user_data/config_futures.json — see letscrash/BTC_STRATEGY_0_1_BYBIT_BRIDGE.md + user_data/config_btc_strategy_0_1_bybit_demo.example.json
# Optional: scripts/btc_analysis_forceenter.py → /api/v1/forceenter (needs force_entry_enable on bot)
# FT_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8081/api/v1
# FT_USER=freqtrader
# FT_PASS=   # same as api_server.password / FT_FUTURES_PASS
# btc+nautilus merge compose defaults NAUTILUS_BYBIT_DEMO to true; set false for mainnet public bars only.
NAUTILUS_BYBIT_DEMO=true
NAUTILUS_BYBIT_TESTNET=false
# Bybit **testnet** (https://testnet.bybit.com/) — Nautilus `run_sygnif_btc_trading_node.py --testnet` (compose profile `btc-testnet`).
# BYBIT_TESTNET_API_KEY=
# BYBIT_TESTNET_API_SECRET=
# Sygnif Nautilus bar node (`nautilus-sygnif-btc-node`, profile btc-nautilus): **default wired order flow**
#   sygnif-finetune-automation / btc_predict_runner → prediction_agent/btc_prediction_output.json
#   → prediction gate (BULLISH / STRONG_BULLISH on consensus_nautilus_enhanced, max age 180m)
#   → nautilus-research sidecar → nautilus_strategy_signal.json (skip short; neutral scales stake)
#   → post-only adaptive BUY on each 5m bar when gates pass (demo). Compose defaults: EXEC_ACK=YES,
#   EXEC_ADAPTIVE=1, EXEC_MAX_ORDERS=150 (bar-node lifetime submit cap; 0 = unlimited), PREDICTION_GATE=1,
#   SIDECAR_GATE=1. With ``nautilus-grid-btc01`` on the same ``BYBIT_DEMO_*`` account, wallet + P/L are **fused**
#   (use ``BYBIT_DEMO_GRID_*`` on the grid only if you want isolation).
# Observe-only (bars + reconciliation, no submits): NAUTILUS_SYGNIF_NODE_EXEC_ADAPTIVE=0
# Prediction-only gate off (still needs bullish sidecar if short): NAUTILUS_SYGNIF_NODE_PREDICTION_GATE=0
# Fixed qty instead of adaptive: NAUTILUS_SYGNIF_NODE_EXEC_ADAPTIVE=0 and add compose override args
#   --exec-order-qty 0.001 (or set NAUTILUS_SYGNIF_NODE_EXEC_* via a override YAML).
# NAUTILUS_SYGNIF_NODE_EXEC_STAKE_FRAC=0.001
# NAUTILUS_SYGNIF_NODE_EXEC_MAX_ORDERS=150
# NAUTILUS_SYGNIF_NODE_EXEC_ADAPTIVE_MIN_QTY=0.001
# NAUTILUS_SYGNIF_NODE_EXEC_ADAPTIVE_MAX_QTY=0.05
# One-way vs hedge (compose passes `--merged-single`; set NAUTILUS_SYGNIF_NODE_EXEC_HEDGE=1 for hedge mode).
# Nautilus ``LiveRiskEngine`` on this node (not trade_overseer/risk_manager.py): default engaged. To disable NT checks:
# NAUTILUS_SYGNIF_NODE_RISK_BYPASS=1
# NAUTILUS_SYGNIF_NODE_RISK_MAX_SUBMIT_RATE=30/00:00:01
# NAUTILUS_SYGNIF_NODE_RISK_MAX_MODIFY_RATE=100/00:00:01
# NAUTILUS_SYGNIF_NODE_RISK_MAX_NOTIONAL_USDT=500
# Optional overrides (defaults already match finetune output path inside Docker):
# NAUTILUS_SYGNIF_NODE_PREDICTION_JSON=/lab/prediction_agent/btc_prediction_output.json
# NAUTILUS_SYGNIF_NODE_PREDICTION_SIGNAL=consensus_nautilus_enhanced
# NAUTILUS_SYGNIF_NODE_PREDICTION_MIN_LOGREG_CONF=0
# NAUTILUS_SYGNIF_NODE_PREDICTION_MAX_AGE_MIN=180
# In-container **live** train+predict on each 5m bar (`btc_predict_live`; compose default `1`). Disable → use JSON file gate:
# NAUTILUS_SYGNIF_NODE_LIVE_PREDICT=0
# NAUTILUS_SYGNIF_NODE_LIVE_DATA_DIR=/lab/btc_specialist_data
# NAUTILUS_SYGNIF_NODE_LIVE_WINDOW=5
# NAUTILUS_SYGNIF_NODE_LIVE_MIN_OHLCV_ROWS=320
# NAUTILUS_SYGNIF_NODE_LIVE_RF_TREES=64
# NAUTILUS_SYGNIF_NODE_LIVE_XGB_N_ESTIMATORS=120
# NAUTILUS_SYGNIF_NODE_LIVE_DIR_C=1.0
# NAUTILUS_SYGNIF_NODE_LIVE_SYMBOL=BTCUSDT
# NAUTILUS_SYGNIF_NODE_LIVE_SEED_LIMIT=800
# NAUTILUS_SYGNIF_NODE_LIVE_MAX_OHLCV_ROWS=1500
# NAUTILUS_SYGNIF_NODE_LIVE_PREDICT_JSON=/lab/prediction_agent/btc_prediction_output.json
# (set to `none` to skip writing JSON from the live loop)
# Optional: newer PyPI pre-releases (not the private GHCR `nautilus-trader:nightly` image): rebuild image with `pip install -U --pre nautilus_trader`.
# Nautilus **live** Bybit demo TradingNode (`research/nautilus_lab/run_bybit_demo_trading_node.py`):
# uses the same BYBIT_DEMO_* keys. Optional Linux auto-exit so `node.run()` does not block forever if quotes stall:
# NAUTILUS_DEMO_SMOKE_AUTO_EXIT_SEC=45
# Nautilus ExecTester on Bybit demo (`run_bybit_demo_exec_tester.py`) — **submits orders**; mandatory gate:
# NAUTILUS_EXEC_TESTER_DEMO_ACK=YES
# (NAUTILUS_GRID_MM_DEMO_ACK is documented next to BYBIT_DEMO_* above — set to YES when running grid MM.)
# Nautilus GridMarketMaker service ``nautilus-grid-btc01`` (profile ``btc-grid-mm``): BTCUSDT linear demo grid.
# ./scripts/start_btc01_nautilus_grid.sh  — use BYBIT_DEMO_GRID_* to isolate from ``freqtrade-btc-0-1``.
# NAUTILUS_GRID_BTC01_TRADE_SIZE=0.001
# NAUTILUS_GRID_BTC01_MAX_POSITION=0.02
# NAUTILUS_GRID_BTC01_NUM_LEVELS=2
# NAUTILUS_GRID_BTC01_GRID_STEP_BPS=15
# NAUTILUS_GRID_BTC01_REQUOTE_BPS=4
# Nautilus Bybit sink interval (seconds). Default 300 = 5m refresh (more API load; ruleprediction timer stays :07 for 1h bar close).
# Use 3600 for hourly polling if you want less load.
NAUTILUS_BYBIT_POLL_SEC=300
NAUTILUS_BTC_BAR_LIMIT=900
# Nautilus → training feed (bar limits + order book / trades caps)
NAUTILUS_TRAINING_BAR_LIMIT_1H=1600
NAUTILUS_TRAINING_BAR_LIMIT_1D=120
NAUTILUS_TRAINING_TRADES_LIMIT=120
NAUTILUS_TRAINING_BOOK_LEVELS=50
NAUTILUS_TRAINING_BOOK_DELTA_CAP=120
# Sidecar loop inside ``run_nautilus_bundled.sh`` (signal JSON refresh).
NAUTILUS_STRATEGY_POLL_SEC=300
# Freqtrade: disable Nautilus TA nudge → ``SYGNIF_NAUTILUS_SIGNAL=0``
# SYGNIF_NAUTILUS_SIGNAL=1

# Host ML (systemd: ruleprediction-pipeline.timer, btc-predict-runner.timer, sygnif-finetune-automation)
# Single-flight lock so only one heavy job uses sklearn/xgb at a time:
# SYGNIF_ML_LOCK_FILE=/home/ubuntu/SYGNIF/user_data/logs/sygnif_ml_pipeline.lock
# Finetune service runs ``scripts/sygnif_finetune_automation.sh --loop`` (persistent; timer starts it ~2min after boot).
# FINETUNE_LOOP_SLEEP_SEC=3600
# FINETUNE_LOCK_BUSY_SLEEP_SEC=90
# FINETUNE_WINDOW_1H=7
# FINETUNE_WINDOW_DAILY=5

# Self-organized horizon check-in (systemd: sygnif-checkin.service / .timer) — fluid ``check``, sparse ``save``
# CHECKIN_SYMBOL=BTC
# CHECKIN_CHECK_INTERVAL_SEC=180
# CHECKIN_FLUID_FAST_SEC=90
# CHECKIN_FLUID_OHLCV_MAX_AGE_SEC=900   # if btc_1h_ohlcv.json newer than this → faster check cadence
# CHECKIN_SNAPSHOT_STALE_SEC=14400      # auto save if snapshot older (seconds)
# CHECKIN_SAVE_MIN_INTERVAL_SEC=10800
# CHECKIN_PREDICTIONS_DIR=/home/ubuntu/.local/share/sygnif-agent/predictions
# CHECKIN_RUN_BTC_24H_PREDICT=1   # after each check, refresh prediction_agent/btc_24h_movement_prediction.json

# Governed forceenter from 24h JSON: ``FORECAST_FORCEENTER_OK=YES python3 scripts/ft_btc_0_1_from_24h_forecast.py``
# FORECAST_STAKE=50
# FORECAST_MIN_CONFIDENCE=40
# FORECAST_ALLOW_LOW_CONF=1

# Freqtrade: ``tradable_balance_ratio`` is a float 0.1–1.0 (default in core docs: 0.99). There is no string ``automated``;
# with ``stake_amount: unlimited`` the bot sizes from wallet using this ratio. Optional Docker override:
# FREQTRADE__TRADABLE_BALANCE_RATIO=0.99

# Freqtrade REST API — use one style consistently (password must match api_server in config).
FREQTRADE_API_USERNAME=freqtrader
FT_SPOT_USER=freqtrader
FT_SPOT_PASS=
# Futures REST (config_futures.json api_server) — use its own password; quote value if it contains spaces or shell-special chars
FT_FUTURES_USER=freqtrader
FT_FUTURES_PASS=
# Shared API password fallback (dashboards try FREQTRADE → FT_* → API_PASSWORD)
API_PASSWORD=
# If the password contains $, write each $ as $$ so Docker Compose does not treat $foo as a variable.
FREQTRADE_API_PASSWORD=

# freqtrade-btc-0-1 REST (host :8185 → container :8085) — direct order: ``python3 scripts/ft_btc_0_1_forceenter.py``
# Paths: POST {FT_BTC_0_1_API_URL}/token/login (Basic auth) then POST …/forceenter (Bearer JWT).
# FT_BTC_0_1_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8185/api/v1
# FT_BTC_0_1_USER=freqtrader
# FT_BTC_0_1_PASS=   # or reuse FT_PASS / API_PASSWORD; else api_server.password in paper-market config
# SYGNIF_FT_BTC_0_1_CONFIG=user_data/config_btc_strategy_0_1_paper_market.json
#
# Optional: ``scripts/btc_analysis_forceenter.py`` → Freqtrade ``forceenter`` from ``btc_prediction_output.json`` (spot long, BULLISH+UP gate).
# FT_BTC_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8282/api/v1
# FT_BTC_USER=freqtrader
# FT_BTC_PASS=
# BTC_ANALYSIS_STAKE=50
# BTC_ANALYSIS_MIN_CONF=55
# Live bot: BTC_ANALYSIS_LIVE_OK=YES

# JWT for Freqtrade API (config_futures api_server.jwt_secret_key)
JWT_SECRET_KEY=
# Legacy optional alias
FT_FUTURES_JWT_SECRET=

# Telegram — spot bot (Freqtrade config.json + optional webhooks)
# notification_handler also accepts FINANCE_BOT_TOKEN + AGENT_CHAT_ID if these are empty.
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=
# Futures bot (config_futures.json telegram + notification_handler webhooks to @sygnifuture_bot)
TELEGRAM_FUTURES_BOT_TOKEN=
TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID=
# Dedicated overseer bot token (recommended for @Sygnif_hedge_bot)
SYGNIF_HEDGE_BOT_TOKEN=

# Freqtrade futures API JWT (must match a stable secret; generate random hex if needed)
FT_FUTURES_JWT_SECRET=

# Optional: Anthropic (notification_handler trade reviews)
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# --- Docker stack: shared network + service URLs (existing “nodes” = container DNS on that network) ---
# All compose services attach to logical network key `sygnif_backend`.
#
# A) Default: Compose creates a bridge named SYGNIF_DOCKER_NETWORK_NAME (default sygnif_backend).
#
# B) “Sygnif Network” — use a pre-created external bridge (same host / EC2):
#    docker network create sygnif_network
#    export COMPOSE_FILE=docker-compose.yml:docker-compose.sygnif-network.yml
#    # optional: SYGNIF_EXTERNAL_NETWORK_NAME=my_custom_name
#    docker compose up -d
#    (Merge file: docker-compose.sygnif-network.yml; SYGNIF_DOCKER_NETWORK_NAME is not used then.)
#
SYGNIF_EXTERNAL_NETWORK_NAME=sygnif_network
# Point these at another stack on the *same* Docker network by using that service’s name, e.g.
#   SYGNIF_SENTIMENT_HTTP_URL=http://my-finance-sidecar:8091/sygnif/sentiment
# To use a finance-agent already listening on the EC2 host (systemd), use host.docker.internal
# (extra_hosts is set in docker-compose for freqtrade / futures / trade-overseer):
#   SYGNIF_SENTIMENT_HTTP_URL=http://host.docker.internal:8091/sygnif/sentiment
#   FINANCE_AGENT_BRIEFING_URL=http://host.docker.internal:8091/briefing
#   OVERSEER_AGENT_URL=http://host.docker.internal:8091/overseer/commentary
SYGNIF_DOCKER_NETWORK_NAME=sygnif_backend
SYGNIF_SENTIMENT_HTTP_URL=http://finance-agent:8091/sygnif/sentiment
# Freqtrade user_data/strategies/SygnifStrategy.py: which implementation backs the SygnifStrategy class.
# sygnif (default) = _SygnifStrategyDefault (HTTP sentiment when configured). ms2 | marketstrategy2 = subclass MarketStrategy2.
# Restart Freqtrade after changing; import-time only.
# SYGNIF_STRATEGY_BACKEND=ms2
# Optional: btc_trend = BTC-only entries via user_data/strategies/btc_trend_regime.py (tag btc_trend_long); unset = full Sygnif stack. See docs/btc_trend_backtest_checklist.md.
# SYGNIF_PROFILE=btc_trend
# Docker: service freqtrade-btc-0-1 sets SYGNIF_PROFILE=btc_trend in-container; start with: docker compose --profile btc-0-1 up -d freqtrade-btc-0-1
FINANCE_AGENT_BRIEFING_URL=http://finance-agent:8091/briefing
# Overseer LLM commentary (POST); same host as finance-agent HTTP when using the bundled image
OVERSEER_AGENT_URL=http://finance-agent:8091/overseer/commentary
OVERSEER_AGENT_TOKEN=
# Trade-overseer: GET /orderbook (Nautilus bundle mount) + POST /ensure_entry (optional flat long)
# OVERSEER_BTC_DATA_DIR=/ro/btc_specialist_data
# OVERSEER_ENSURE_TOKEN=generate-a-long-random-secret
# OVERSEER_ENSURE_STAKE=50
# OVERSEER_ENSURE_IGNORE_SIGNAL=0
# OVERSEER_ENSURE_LIVE_OK=YES
# Trade overseer Bybit USDT linear hedge (demo api-demo.bybit.com + BYBIT_DEMO_* unless mainnet):
#   POST http://127.0.0.1:8090/bybit/hedge/switch-mode  body {"symbol":"BTCUSDT","mode":"hedge"|"oneway"}
#   POST http://127.0.0.1:8090/bybit/hedge/order       body {"symbol":"BTCUSDT","side":"Buy","qty":"0.001","positionIdx":1}
#   GET  http://127.0.0.1:8090/bybit/hedge/positions?symbol=BTCUSDT
# Header: X-Overseer-Hedge-Token (or reuse X-Overseer-Ensure-Token if OVERSEER_HEDGE_TOKEN unset).
# OVERSEER_HEDGE_TOKEN=
# OVERSEER_BYBIT_HEDGE_MAINNET=YES
# OVERSEER_HEDGE_LIVE_OK=YES
# Trade overseer ``plays.json``: keep only BTC/USDT play blocks + BTC market_context lines; match plays→trades for BTC pairs only.
# SYGNIF_PLAYS_BTC_USDT_ONLY=1
# Optional /briefing (8091): R01/R02 lines when training_channel_output.json or rule registry mtimes change (in-process dedupe).
# SYGNIF_BRIEFING_INCLUDE_RULE_PREDICT=1
# Optional: one compact line from btc_prediction_output.json when file age < SYGNIF_BRIEFING_BTC_PREDICT_MAX_AGE_H (default 24).
# SYGNIF_BRIEFING_INCLUDE_BTC_PREDICT=1
# prediction_horizon_check.py save: append horizon row to prediction_agent/rule_tag_journal.csv when set.
# RULE_TAG_JOURNAL=1
# RULE_TAG_JOURNAL_TAG=BTC-0.1-R03

# Optional: override Freqtrade API base URLs if your trader containers use different hostnames
# FT_SPOT_URL=http://freqtrade:8080/api/v1
# FT_FUTURES_URL=http://freqtrade-futures:8081/api/v1

# Finance-agent HTTP container: LLM (same as Telegram bot stack)
# CURSOR_API_KEY=
# CURSOR_AGENT_REPOSITORY=https://github.com/you/SYGNIF
# CURSOR_AGENT_REF=main
# Optional: LLM_BACKEND=ollama + OLLAMA_MODEL=... if not using Cursor Cloud

# Optional: NewHedge.io metrics API (token required — unauthenticated returns 401). Used by finance_agent/newhedge_client.py and scripts/market_open_context_report.py.
# NEWHEDGE_API_KEY=

# Optional: CoinGecko Pro — `x-cg-pro-api-key` for `pull_btc_extended_history.py` (Pro host). Free tier: leave unset.
# COINGECKO_API_KEY=

# Optional: Crypto APIs — https://app.cryptoapis.io/api-keys — header X-API-Key; BTC mainnet + market-data via finance_agent/cryptoapis_client.py → btc_cryptoapis_foundation.json (pull_btc_context.py).
# cryptoapi_Token=

# Dashboard BTC context: run pull with finance-agent LLM analysis (same llm_analyze + KB as /finance-agent). Set 0 for fast pull / no Cursor.
# CRYPTO_CONTEXT_LLM=1
# Optional: only run LLM when cursor-agent-worker is healthy (GET CURSOR_WORKER_HEALTH_URL, default :8093/healthz). Else heuristic fallback.
# CRYPTO_CONTEXT_REQUIRE_WORKER=1

# Orthogonal / nn-zero-to-hero — finance-agent GET /training discovers Jupyter + paths
# ORTHOGONAL_TRAINING_BASE=http://host.docker.internal:8890
# ORTHOGONAL_TRAINING_HOST=host.docker.internal
# ORTHOGONAL_TRAINING_PORT=8890
# NN_ZERO_TO_HERO_ROOT=/home/ubuntu/nn-zero-to-hero

# Sentiment MLP (train: finance_agent/scripts/train_sentiment_mlp.py → user_data/finance_agent/sentiment_mlp.npz)
# SENTIMENT_MLP_ENABLED=1
# SENTIMENT_MLP_WEIGHTS=/app/finance_agent_models/sentiment_mlp.npz
# SENTIMENT_MLP_ALPHA=0.45
# Train with real closes: python3 finance_agent/scripts/train_sentiment_mlp.py --freqtrade-db user_data/tradesv3-futures.sqlite --print-analysis
# Analysis only: python3 finance_agent/scripts/analyze_closed_trades.py --db user_data/tradesv3-futures.sqlite --json

# Optional: Giansn/Network NN sidecar — GET body is appended to `/finance-agent network nodes` and `/sygnif` cycle (truncated)
# NETWORK_NN_STATUS_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8095/nn-status

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Reverse SSH tunnel (EC2 → gateway) — “constant host” for a local dashboard
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# EC2 runs ssh -N -R … so your VPS/home box exposes a port that forwards here.
# On the gateway: optional sshd_config `GatewayPorts clientspecified` or `yes` if REMOTE_BIND=0.0.0.0.
# Install unit: sudo cp systemd/sygnif-reverse-tunnel.service /etc/systemd/system/ && sudo systemctl daemon-reload
# Enable:     sudo systemctl enable --now sygnif-reverse-tunnel
# Disable:   sudo systemctl disable --now sygnif-reverse-tunnel
#
# SYGNIF_REVERSE_TUNNEL_ENABLE=1
# SYGNIF_REVERSE_TUNNEL_GATEWAY=ubuntu@your-vps.example.com
# Optional dedicated key (chmod 600): SYGNIF_REVERSE_TUNNEL_IDENTITY_FILE=/home/ubuntu/.ssh/sygnif_tunnel_ed25519
# SYGNIF_REVERSE_TUNNEL_REMOTE_BIND=127.0.0.1
# SYGNIF_REVERSE_TUNNEL_REMOTE_PORT=19891
# SYGNIF_REVERSE_TUNNEL_LOCAL_HOST=127.0.0.1
# SYGNIF_REVERSE_TUNNEL_LOCAL_PORT=8888
# Public bind on gateway (needs sshd GatewayPorts): SYGNIF_REVERSE_TUNNEL_REMOTE_BIND=0.0.0.0
# Use an SSH key for the tunnel user (BatchMode=yes — no password prompt under systemd).
